{{Doomwiki|stealth monsters}}
'''Stealth monsters''' are monsters which are normally invisible. They become briefly visible when they receive damage, fade out of visibility when calling [[A_Look]], [[A_LookEx]], [[A_Chase]], [[A_ExtChase]], [[A_FastChase]], [[A_VileChase]]. They fade in, on the other hand, when calling [[A_FaceTarget]], [[A_FaceTracer]], [[A_FaceMaster]], [[A_MonsterRail]], [[A_CustomRailgun]], or [[A_CPosAttack]]. (Note that practically all attack functions call [[A_FaceTarget]].) Finally, the monsters become and remain visible when calling [[A_Fall]], [[A_NoBlocking]], or [[A_FreezeDeath]].

Creating a stealth monster in [[ZDoom]] is easy: merely adding the {{Flag|STEALTH}} flag and giving it an {{property|Alpha}} of 0 is enough. Note, however, that when a stealth monster is visible, its {{Property|RenderStyle|render style}} will always be "normal". A fuzzy, shaded, additive, translucent, etc. stealth monster will not work; the stealth implementation directly changing the actor's render style.

By default, ZDoom provides stealth variants of the ''[[Doom II]]'' monsters except the {{Class|spectre}}, the {{Class|cyberdemon}}, the {{Class|SpiderMastermind|spiderdemon}}, the {{Class|PainElemental|pain elemental}} and the Easter eggs {{Class|CommanderKeen|Commander Keen}} and {{Class|WolfensteinSS|Wolfenstein SS}}:
*{{Class|StealthArachnotron}}
*{{Class|StealthArchvile}}
*{{Class|StealthBaron}}
*{{Class|StealthCacodemon}}
*{{Class|StealthChaingunGuy}}
*{{Class|StealthDemon}}
*{{Class|StealthHellKnight}}
*{{Class|StealthDoomImp}}
*{{Class|StealthFatso}}
*{{Class|StealthRevenant}}
*{{Class|StealthShotgunGuy}}
*{{Class|StealthZombieMan}}
A stealth spectre would be indistinguishable from a stealth demon, stealth bosses would be quite unfair, and the Easter eggs' presence in mod is generally frowned upon as an amateurish mistake.
